  "description": "Claire and Tom converted their entire back lawn in January 2024 after the December 2023 heatwave killed most of what was growing. Rather than replant with the same, they asked a different question: what was here before the lawn? The answer -- a Wet Sclerophyll Forest remnant, with Merri Creek just 200 metres away -- changed everything. The garden is now in its second year of establishment, the canopy beginning to close, the understorey thickening, the burrowing bee population they documented in autumn 2024 now reliably returning. It is not finished. It is working.",
